Package net.ashwork.functionality.throwable.abstracts.consumer

This package holds the basic abstract throwing Consumers.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AbstractThrowingConsumer0<H extends AbstractThrowingConsumer0.Handler,C extends AbstractThrowingConsumer0<H,C>>
    Represents an operation that accepts no arguments and returns no result or throws a throwable.
    AbstractThrowingConsumer0.Handler
    Represents a handler that takes in the outer throwable's parameters and the throwable and operates safely.
    AbstractThrowingConsumer1<T1,H extends AbstractThrowingConsumer1.Handler<T1>,C extends AbstractThrowingConsumer1<T1,H,C>>
    Represents an operation that accepts one argument and returns no result or throws a throwable.
    AbstractThrowingConsumer1.Handler<T1>
    Represents a handler that takes in the outer throwable's parameters and the throwable and operates safely.
    AbstractThrowingConsumer2<T1,T2,H extends AbstractThrowingConsumer2.Handler<T1,T2>,C extends AbstractThrowingConsumer2<T1,T2,H,C>>
    Represents an operation that accepts two arguments and returns no result or throws a throwable.
    AbstractThrowingConsumer2.Handler<T1,T2>
    Represents a handler that takes in the outer throwable's parameters and the throwable and operates safely.
    AbstractThrowingConsumerN<H extends AbstractThrowingConsumerN.Handler,C extends AbstractThrowingConsumerN<H,C>>
    Represents an operation that accepts n arguments and returns no result or throws a throwable.
    AbstractThrowingConsumerN.Handler
    Represents a handler that takes in the outer throwable's parameters and the throwable and operates safely.

Package net.ashwork.functionality.throwable.abstracts.consumer Description

This package holds the basic abstract throwing Consumers. Some functional interfaces are specialized such that the type parameters are primitives with additional type prefixes.
